$ Orca.exe

`C:\Program Files (x86)\Orca\Orca.exe` can be used to create and edit Windows Installer Database files (`.msi`, `.msm`, `.msp`, `.mst`, `.cub`, `.pcp`).

{ Installing

  { Windows SDK

   `Orca.exe` can be installed using the â†’ Windows/development/Kits/Software-Development[Windows SDK] feature `OptionId.MSIInstallTools` and then executing `C:\Program Files (x86)\Windows Kits\10\bin\10.0.26100.0\x86\Orca-x86_en-us.msi` (or similar).

  }
  { Visual Studio

    After installing Visual Studio 2022 community edition with Windows 11 SDK, I found `Orca-x86_en-us.msi` under `C:\Program Files (x86)\Windows Kits\10\bin\10.0.26100.0\x86`.
    
    Executing this MSI installed `Orca.exe`.

  }
}
